Recommending Age of Wonders 3, not Planetfall.
My experience:
//I need to spend $30 to get $5 off. Planetfall is on sale! It's basically like I'd be losing money if I didn't buy this now.
Uninstall AoW3 to make room on SSD, install AoWPF.
- Play for 30 minutes.

//Oh, cool! I like this new idea for managing cities! And this unit mod idea is fun too! The diplomacy with neutrals is so interesting! Amazonians must be easy mode - look at these ranged units and healing spells! No, the mining group is easy mode - I get so many free resources!
- Play for a few more hours.

//Wait, I can only be friendly toward one neutral faction? This is as far as the tech tree goes? Why does the setting grate on my nerves? Do I have to finish trying out every race and class? Every win condition? Can't I just go back to AoW3?
- Thank AoWPF for reminding me how delightful a game AoW3 was.
- Uninstall

66832959.review:
This should be neutral review, but since Steam does not offer such option, in current game state I won't recommend bying.

Game is just not catchy. AoW2 had soul, this one.. not. It's marketing product, not product of passion. I mean on paper there's everything you love in series - city/empire building, various tech & racial stuff, complex tactical battles, RPG-like heroes development and so on...
But every feature is flawed:
Character progression got even more stripped than in AoW3 (compared to AoW2);
Tactical combat is almost like in 3, but city battles lost their walls (seems Triumph can't code good enough AI to use them);
Races are mostly reskins of AoW3 races;
Techs are mostly mirrored versions of each other, I mean they don't determine your playstyle that much as expected to;
Cities became even more genereic than (how this even possible?)

New campaign is good and bad at same time. Good part is that maps are quite large and support various completion paths and (mostly) you can solve situation in the way you would like it. But there's no over-arching big story(well it is, but it is VERY bland) like it was in AoW2 and in some sort in AoW3(which had also like AoWP issues in that matter)

Exploration is almost killed(they've tried to address that issue in 1.2 patch to some avail).
Map-locations are much less impactful then they were in previous games.

However I liked regions and outpost mechanics and love setting idea(tho it is not atmospheric as it could be) and in general game plays mostly like AoW3. But... "mostly".

Thus I recommend waiting for next content DLCs to release to see if the devs can put some soul into this game. It has potential, but right now it's more boring than entertaining after first 30 hours(which is not that much for a strategy game)
